`IllegalReferenceCountException` when expected conditions are not met, preventing potential misuse. Nullifying `parent` and `rootParent` for garbage collection helps address a possible memory leak issue, as reported in netty/netty#14247, ensuring that the memory is cleaned up properly and improving overall memory management.\n\n> Is this description stale? Ask me to generate a new description by commenting `/korbit-generate-pr-description`\n<!-- Korbit AI PR Description End -->\n\n\n___\n\n### **PR Type**\nbug_fix, enhancement\n\n\n___\n\n### **Description**\n- Added null checks in the `unwrap()` method to throw `IllegalReferenceCountException` when `rootParent` is null, preventing misuse.\n- Updated the `deallocate()` method to nullify `parent` and `rootParent`, facilitating garbage collection and addressing potential memory leaks.\n- Improved memory management by ensuring that recycled buffers do not hold references to their parents, aiding in leak detection.\n\n\n\n___\n\n\n\n### **Changes walkthrough** üìù\n<table><thead><tr><th></th><th align=\"left\">Relevant files</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>Bug fix</strong></td><td><table>\n<tr>\n  <td>\n    <details>\n      <summary><strong>AbstractPooledDerivedByteBuf.java</strong><dd><code>Improve memory management and exception handling in buffer </code><br><code>deallocation</code></dd></summary>\n<hr>\n\nbuffer/src/main/java/io/netty/buffer/AbstractPooledDerivedByteBuf.java\n\n<li>Added null checks in <code>unwrap()</code> to prevent <br><code>IllegalReferenceCountException</code>.<br> <li> Updated <code>deallocate()</code> to nullify <code>parent</code> and <code>rootParent</code> for garbage <br>collection.<br> <li> Imported <code>IllegalReferenceCountException</code>.<br>\n\n\n</details>\n\n\n  </td>\n  <td><a href=\"https://github.com/maorethians/netty/pull/18/files#diff-aec887594c62456757ec107de1ffc61cdd4525cedd838f6a62229829b228f271\">+7/-0</a>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; </td>\n\n</tr>\n</table></td></tr></